                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="anyhoo_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">an informal way of saying or writing ‘anyhow’ (when it is used to change the subject or return to a subject), for example in conversation or an email or text to a friend</span></span><ul class="examples" hclass="examples" htag="ul"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x"> Anyhoo, where was I? Oh yeah, Dave and his new girlfriend …</span></li></ul> <span class="un" un="help">You should not write this form in formal or standard writing.</span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
